.*A*
KWIC IS NORMALLY USED TO GENERATE A KWIC INDEX TO CP6 MODULES
FROM AN INPUT FILE OF *M* RECORDS - OR A KWIC INDEX TO THE
ARCH FILE USING THE ARCH INDEX AS INPUT. GIVEN ANY INPUT FILE
AND THE COLUMNS TO GENERATE THE INDEX FROM - KWIC OUTPUTS A
KWIC INDEX.
!SET A-CARD <input_file>
!SET TEMPFILE <temp_file>
!SET PRINTER <print_file or LP>
!KWIC.X
THE PROGRAM WILL ASK FOR A TITLE AND COLUMNS TO SORT.
.*K* XINDEX
KWIC.X
.*R*
AID=UTILITY
.*R*
INDEXING
.*R*
.*K* XINDEX_ABSTRACT
TOOL=KWIC
.*R*
Generates a KWIC (KeyWord In Context) index to CP-6
modules from an input file of *M* records, or a KWIC index to the ARCH
file using the ARCH index as input.
.*K* CHANGES Changes changes
08/12/82
.*R*
Updated to work on B03.  Apparently did NOT work with new COBOL library.
.*B*
.*X*
